mentalist way of reading texts regarded as sacred.To explain and clarify the approach of the crafty reader, the author analyzes a wide-ranging selection of texts by figures at the margins of the literary and cultural canon, including Norman Rockwell, Anaïs Nin, Dashiell Hammett, and J. K. Rowling. Throughout his discussion Scholes emphasizes how concepts of genre affect the reading process and how they may work to exclude certain texts from the cultural canon and curriculum.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aBooks and readingxEnglish-speaking countries. 0aBooks and readingzEnglish-speaking countries. 0aCriticismxEnglish-speaking countries. 0aCriticismzEnglish-speaking countries. 0aCritiquexPays anglophones. 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aEsthétique de la réception. 0aGenres littéraires. 0aLiterary form. 0aLiteraturexAppreciation. 0aLittérature américainexHistoire et critiquexThéorie, etc. 0aLittérature anglaisexHistoire et critiquexThéorie, etc. 0aLittératurexAppréciation. 0aLivres et lecturexPays anglophones. 0aReader-response criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Books & Reading.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300128871423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300128871.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles